  a value."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.357155Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23938-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A return value is a value that is returned to the calling program."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.357160Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23938-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Arguments are values provided to a subroutine at the time it is called."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.357164Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23938-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Subroutine parameters are values used by the subroutine that are passed from the
  arguments when it is called."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.357168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24085-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Web pages can be broken into sections called divisions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.361785Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24085-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "HTML elements can be labelled with class names."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.361789Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24085-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Divisions of a web page can be formatted independently in CSS via an assigned class
  name."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.361793Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24116-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Relative and absolute cell references are used in spreadsheet formulas to control
  how cell addresses change when copied."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.361856Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24116-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A relative reference changes automatically when the formula is copied to another
  cell."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.361860Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24116-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An absolute reference stays fixed on one cell, even when the formula is
  replicated."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.361863Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24116-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using the correct type of reference helps ensure formulas calculate correctly when
  using tools like the fill handle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.361867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24001-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Being online poses a number of risks."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.362551Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24001-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "These risks can be categorised into content, contact, conduct and commerce."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.362555Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24001-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "These risks can be reduced and mitigated by a user's actions and behaviour."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.362560Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24001-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Online safety is about taking practical steps to protect yourself online."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.362566Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23953-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A string is a collection of characters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363023Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23953-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """String handling is using techniques and built-in functions to find out information
  about strings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363028Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23953-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The len() function is used to return the length of a string."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363032Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23953-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The index number is used to retrieve a single character from a specified position in
  a string."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363035Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23953-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "For loops can be used to iterate through some or all of the items in a string."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363039Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23956-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Data structures are used to store data in an organised and accessible way."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363098Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23956-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Data structures can be static or dynamic."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363102Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23956-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Static data structures reserve memory locations for a set amount of data. Their size
  cannot change."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363106Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23956-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Dynamic data structures are more flexible. The memory capacity is not fixed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363110Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23903-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Selection is used when there is more than one possible path for a program to
  follow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23903-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Selection is carried out using if, elif and else statements."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363118Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23903-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A selection statement will check if a condition returns as True or False."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23903-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Multi-path selection is used when there is more than one path for a program to
  follow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363127Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23921-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Trace tables are used to record how the values of variables change during the
  execution of a program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363132Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23921-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Trace tables and while loops help debug programs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.363136Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23904-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Arithmetic expressions are used to calculate values."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.365018Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23904-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Arithmetic expressions can be used in selection statements. Expressions either
  return as True or False."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.365023Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23904-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In real division there is no remainder because the entire value is divided."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.365027Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23904-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Integer division is when any remainder of a division is discarded."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.365031Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23904-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Modulo division (MOD) will return only the remainder of a division."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.365035Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24065-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """SQL stands for Structured Query Language. It is a language used to communicate with
  a database."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.366717Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24065-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You can use SQL to manipulate databases and retrieve records."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.366721Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24065-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An SQL INSERT statement allows you to add data into pre-existing tables."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.366725Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24065-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An SQL UPDATE statement allows you to modify records."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.366729Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24065-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Existing records can be deleted from a table by using an SQL DELETE statement."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.366733Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23998-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some content online can potentially be harmful."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.367455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23998-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some online content can be distressing or upsetting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.367458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23998-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some content is illegal to share or can be used to facilitate online crime."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.367463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23998-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In the UK, there are a number of laws that govern online content and online
  crimes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.367467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23999-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Not all internet regulation is the removal of illegal content; some of it may
  instead be considered censorship."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.367493Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23999-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Laws around access to information online differ across the world."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.367497Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23999-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Technologies can be used to help citizens in areas with high levels of internet
  censorship to access information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.367500Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23943-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A project brief specifies what the requirements of a program are."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.370143Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23943-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A structure chart is a diagram used to design the structure of the subroutines
  required for completing a program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.370147Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23943-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A flowchart is a visual representation of a program."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.370151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23931-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A logic statement is a statement that evaluates to either True or False."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.371440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23931-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You can write a logic statement to represent an outcome where the result is
  dependent on Boolean variables."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.371444Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23931-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Boolean logic combines multiple logic statements into an expression that is either
  True or False."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.371448Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24014-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The performance of LLMs is highly dependent on how users craft their prompts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.375351Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24014-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Prompts should be specific and clear to enable the model to interpret what
  you want."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.375354Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24014-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Prompts should provide relevant context or examples so the model can generate more
  accurate and tailored responses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.375358Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24014-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """LLMs can reflect biases from their training data, so responses should be critically
  evaluated and cross-checked."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.375362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23939-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A procedure is a named block of code that performs a specific task."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.378673Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23939-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Procedures are designed to run a sequence of code that does not return any value to
  the calling program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.378677Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23939-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In order to run a procedure, it must be called by the main program."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.378681Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29431-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """As programs grow in complexity it becomes useful to structure them in a way that is
  more manageable for the programmer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29431-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A structured approach to programming uses a module approach where a program is
  seperated into subprograms."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29431-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A program can be decomposed into smaller subprograms that are easier to solve
  indepedently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380911Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29431-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The interface determines how data will be passed in and out of the subprogram."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380915Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24083-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Effective design of a webpage considers usability, readability, accessibility."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380919Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24083-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A website is a collection of web pages hyperlinked together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24083-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Website design creation focuses on the layout of pages and the navigation between
  them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380927Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24083-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Effective implementation of a web site design includes an organised file structure
  for the resources on each page."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24084-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "CSS describes the styling that is applied to HTML."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380955Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24084-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Properties of HTML tags are changed in a CSS file linked to a web page."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380959Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24084-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """CSS provides consistency of design across the pages of a website in a single
  location."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380963Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24084-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "CSS can control text and background formatting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.380967Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29438-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Implementation of solution is where you take a plan and create the solution."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.385310Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29438-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A program should be tested with a range of test data."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.385314Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29438-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Erroneous data is data that should not be accepted by the program or it will cause
  an error."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.385318Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29438-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Boundary test data is data of the correct type which is on the very edge of being
  valid."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.385322Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29438-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Normal data is data that should be accepted by a program. This is data that you
  would expect a user to enter."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.385326Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24099-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A digital artefact is anything that has been created and is stored digitally."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.386480Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24099-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A physical artefact is something you can touch, see and use in the real world."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.386484Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24099-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A physical artefact can be created when a digital artefact is printed and used."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.386488Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24100-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Initiation is about understanding the problem or brief, including audience research
  and defining success."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.386513Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24100-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Planning involves mapping out how you will solve the problem and create your product
  or solution."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.386517Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24100-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Execution is the creating stage where plans are turned into reality."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.386521Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24100-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The testing and evaluation stage involves critically assessing the end product to
  identify areas for improvement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.386525Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24100-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Closure or presentation is about bringing the project to a formal close and sharing
  the final work."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.386529Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24118-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Data validation is a tool in spreadsheets that controls what kind of data can be
  entered into a cell."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.387258Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24118-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is used to help prevent mistakes, such as typing the wrong word or entering
  numbers outside a set range."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.387262Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24118-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Various types of criteria can be used in data validation, such as text, dates and
  number ranges."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.387266Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24118-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Data validation can show helpful messages when users make an error."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.387270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24118-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using data validation helps keep data accurate and consistent."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.387274Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23940-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The scope of a variable determines where it can be accessed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.388944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23940-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A local variable is a variable that is only accessible within a specific part of a
  program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.388948Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23940-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A global variable can be accessed anywhere in a program for the duration of the
  program's execution."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.388954Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24126-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Planning tools manage time and tasks in a project by visually organising when and
  how activities should be completed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.390622Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24126-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A Gantt chart is a timeline-based planning tool."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.390626Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24126-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A PERT chart is a network diagram that uses nodes and arrows to show task flow."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.390630Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24105-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """All websites are built using HTML — even if site-building software is used, HTML is
  in the background."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.392049Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24105-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """CSS is used for creating styles to use throughout the process of creating a
  website."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.392053Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24105-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Web design software allows a drag-and-drop approach to creating a website."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.392057Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24105-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You need a domain name and hosting to create your own website."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.392061Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29432-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A procedure is a named block of code that performs a specific task."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.393909Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29432-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Procedures are designed to run a sequence of code that does not return any value to
  the calling program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.393913Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29432-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In order to run a procedure, it must be called by the main program."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.393917Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23917-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Secondary storage types are optical, magnetic and solid state."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.394794Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23917-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The most commonly used secondary storage devices are optical storage using lasers,
  and solid state using 0s and 1s."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.394798Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23932-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A logic circuit is a set of two or more logic gates that are connected to implement
  more complex logic."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395824Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23932-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A digital electronic circuit in a computer system is used to realise solutions to
  problems."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395828Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23932-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A circuit diagram illustrates how logic gates are combined to create digital
  circuits."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.395832Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24128-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A hierarchy diagram shows how a user will move from one part of a system to
  another."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397576Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24128-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You can create a working digital tool using presentation software by adding
  hyperlinks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24128-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Editing the master slide means you can set a style once and use it across all your
  slides."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397587Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24128-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Good products are made with purpose and audience in mind."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.397592Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29437-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A project brief specifies what the requirements of a program are."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.400088Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29437-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A structure chart is a diagram used to design the structure of the subprograms
  required for completing a program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.400092Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29437-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A flowchart is a visual representation of a program."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.400096Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24030-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are different modes for opening a file, r (read), w (write) and a
  (append)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403662Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24030-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When you open a file in write mode, it creates a new file. If the file already
  exists then the file will be overwritten."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403667Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24030-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When you open a file and write to a file in append mode, it will add to the existing
  contents of the file."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403671Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24030-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is good practice to close the file once written to. Some IDEs will not write to a
  file until it is closed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403675Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24108-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Motors convert electrical energy into motion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24108-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Microcontrollers cannot drive motors directly."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24108-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Motor drivers are needed to safely control motors."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24108-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The direction and speed of motors can be controlled with code."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403694Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24103-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The two main types of digital graphics are called raster and vector."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403698Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24103-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Raster and bitmap are interchangeable terms used for the same type of image."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403702Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24103-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Lossy means quality is lost if the image is resized."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403706Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24103-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Lossless means no quality is lost when resized."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.403710Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24069-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Databases are designed to store large volumes of data."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419536Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24069-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This data could hold sensitive and personal information about individuals."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419541Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24069-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are a number of methods that can be used to protect data held in
  databases."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419547Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24069-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """These methods include user access controls, data encryption, regular audits and data
  anonymisation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419551Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24069-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Regulations are laws that tell organisations how they must handle personal data to
  keep it safe and private."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419555Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23929-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Boolean logic is a form of algebra where all logical relations can be expressed as a
  combination of AND, OR and NOT."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419576Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23929-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A logic gate is a fundamental component of a digital circuit."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419580Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23929-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each logic gate has a symbol, which is used in circuit diagrams."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419584Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23929-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Each logic gate has a unique truth table that shows how the output changes with
  different inputs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.419589Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24130-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A project brief is analysed to determine what the project is about and what needs to
  be completed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.421199Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24130-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """User requirements are the features or outcomes the client expects from the
  project."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.421205Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24130-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Project documentation can be used to set out what you hope to achieve during a
  project."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.421210Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24101-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An asset list is a document or spreadsheet containing details about the assets
  required for the project."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.422067Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24101-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A flowchart might be used to help show the process that can be followed from one
  instruction or action to another."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.422071Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24101-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A mood board could include colour schemes, fonts, imagery, textures, and fonts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.422075Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23997-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In the UK there are a number of laws designed to protect privacy."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.426351Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23997-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some laws like the Investigatory Powers Act (2016) take away privacy rights in
  certain circumstances."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.426355Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23997-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Laws are used to prosecute and may deter some individuals from committing crimes,
  but do not stop laws being broken."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.426361Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24005-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Cloud computing offers data storage, the ability to collaborate and backup and
  disaster recovery."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.427528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24005-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "SaaS (software as a service) allows users to access applications via the web."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.427532Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24005-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Cloud computing offers accessibility as it allows users to access services from
  anywhere with an internet connection."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.427536Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24042-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "IP addresses identify devices on a network."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.430017Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24042-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "DHCP assigns IP addresses automatically."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.430022Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24042-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """DNS converts domain names into IP addresses, which identify devices on the
  internet."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.430026Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24129-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The evaluation stage is where you reflect on how well a project went."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.437472Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24129-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The evaluation stage helps you understand what worked well and what could be
  improved for next time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.437476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24129-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Test tables can be used to check that everything works properly in a digital
  tool."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.437480Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24129-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By looking back at your SMART goals and planning tool, you can see if you completed
  everything you set out to do."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.437486Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24129-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Every good project includes reflection as part of the process."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.437491Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23996-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our online reputations are valuable to organisations."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438272Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23996-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Organisations collect data to streamline services and target advertisements."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23996-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Data can even be used to change the content that is shown to us online."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438285Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23996-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A key tool for harnessing the value of this information is big data."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438289Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23996-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Big data is the term used to describe large data sets that are analysed in order to
  identify patterns and trends."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438294Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23912-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An embedded computer system has a specific task or set of tasks to complete."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438898Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23912-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A general purpose computer system has a range of purposes defined by a user
  interaction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438902Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23912-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Application software is developed to perform end-user tasks."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438906Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23912-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Utility software manages specific tasks on a computer system."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.438910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24056-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Protocols are sets of rules that are followed to allow communication to take
  place."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.584515Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24056-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "IP adresses are given to devices normally by the router on a local network."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.584520Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23919-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Data centres are large collections of servers used to store, manage and process
  data."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585870Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23919-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Data centres consume vast amounts of electricity and require extensive cooling."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23919-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """E-waste is placed in landfills where chemicals leak into the surrounding
  environment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23888-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An IDE includes tools such as a code editor, debugger, and compiler to streamline
  software development."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23888-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Features like syntax highlighting, auto-completion, and error detection improve
  coding efficiency and accuracy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585889Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24051-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Software testing checks whether a program works correctly, meets requirements and is
  free from bugs or errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585894Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24051-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Integration testing checks whether different parts of the program work together
  correctly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585899Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24051-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Black box testing tests without knowing how the code works inside."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585907Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24051-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """White box testing tests with full knowledge of the code, often focusing on logic and
  structure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585913Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24051-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """After testing, debugging can take place to remove and correct errors in a
  program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.585920Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24046-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A project brief explains what the program should do."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.591138Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24046-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Analysing a brief means looking closely at the information to understand exactly
  what the project needs to achieve."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.591145Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24046-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Functional requirements describe what the program should do, like inputs, outputs,
  processes and key features."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.591151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23900-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Data structures are used to help store, organise and manipulate data to solve
  problems efficiently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.597890Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23900-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Arrays are static data structures that can store data of a single type in indexed
  elements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.597897Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23900-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lists are dynamic data structures that can store data of different types in indexed
  elements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.597901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23900-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The choice of data structure depends on the specific needs of the algorithm or
  problem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.597905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23933-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A truth table is a way of summarising and checking the logic of a circuit."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.597909Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23933-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The table shows all possible combinations of inputs and, for each combination, the
  output the circuit will produce."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.597913Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23895-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Computational thinking is a systematic approach to solving problems."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.608233Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23895-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Decomposition is used to break down a large problem into smaller subproblems."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.608237Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23895-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Abstraction is used to focus on the important details of a problem."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.608241Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23895-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Algorithmic thinking is used to create a series of logical, step-by-step
  instructions to solve a problem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.608245Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23886-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Computers run programs and code exactly as it is written."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.608294Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23886-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Low-level languages provide direct control over hardware."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.608298Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23886-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "High-level languages use abstraction to make programming more human-readable."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.608304Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24047-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Software design principles are guidelines that help developers write clean,
  efficient and maintainable code."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.609024Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24047-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Good design makes code easier to read, test and change."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.609028Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23916-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "RAM is volatile and ROM is non volatile."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.609351Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23916-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "RAM stores data and instructions currently in use."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.609356Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23916-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "ROM stores the start-up/boot-up instructions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.609360Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23916-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Cache is used for frequently used instructions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.609364Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24048-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Structured design is the process of planning a program in detail before you start to
  write any code."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611559Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24048-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This design stage is essential for developers to understand the program's
  requirements and how it will function."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611566Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24048-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Tools like flowcharts provide a visual representation of a program's logic."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611570Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24048-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Pseudocode offers a text-based, step-by-step description of a program's
  operation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611575Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24048-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Designing a program this way helps to prevent mistakes, saves time and makes final
  code easier to write and understand."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24086-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Wireframe designs can be used to plan the layout of a web page."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24086-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The CSS box model explains how HTML elements are structured and spaced on a web
  page."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611587Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24086-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The position of divisions can be controlled by using the floating property
  of a tag."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611594Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24086-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Divisions can be placed inside other divisions to control groups of content."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.611598Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23913-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Operating systems (OS) regulate interactions between software and computer system
  hardware."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.617967Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23913-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An operating system enables a user interface like Windows to run."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.617972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23913-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Security management enables different users to use a device with different access
  rights and file storage."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.617978Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23901-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Algorithmic bias is when an algorithm produces unfair or discriminatory outcomes
  that favour some groups over others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618830Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23901-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using poor quality data in algorithms can lead to inaccurate results, unreliable
  predictions, or biased outcomes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618834Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23901-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Algorithms can become biased if the design of the algorithm instructions are
  biased."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618838Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23901-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By aiming to understand sources of bias algorithmic, bias can be reduced as much as
  possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618842Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24045-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The software development life cycle (SDLC) defines the main stages of software
  development."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618992Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24045-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Planning is a vital stage because it helps developers organise their ideas, avoid
  mistakes and work more efficiently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618996Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24045-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Real-world programming projects are rarely perfect the first time so planning for
  changes and improvements is essential."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.619000Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23899-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Trace tables can be used to walkthrough and understand the logic of an
  algorithm."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.619004Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23899-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Trace tables can be used to help find logical errors in algorithms."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.619008Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28995-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Boolean logic is the foundation of all digital circuit design."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.621505Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28995-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A logic circuit is a set of two or more logic gates that are connected to implement
  more complex logic."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.621511Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-28995-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A digital electronic circuit in a computer system is typically made up of millions
  of logic gates."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.621515Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24053-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To evaluate a project means to look back at what you have created and judge how well
  it meets the requirements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.621519Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24053-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using a rubric can help you check each part of your work against clear success
  criteria."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.621523Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24053-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A strong evaluation highlights what went well and what could be improved."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.621528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-24053-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It helps you learn from the project and develop your skills for future programming
  work."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.621534Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23930-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Boolean logic is the foundation of all digital circuit design."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.628571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23930-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A logic circuit is a set of two or more logic gates that are connected to implement
  more complex logic."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.628575Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23930-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A digital electronic circuit in a computer system is typically made up of millions
  of logic gates."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.628579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23897-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Algorithms can be represented by flowcharts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.632038Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23897-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Flowcharts use symbols to visually represent logic and data."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.632043Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23897-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Developing an algorithm's logic before coding makes problem solving easier."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.632047Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23898-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Algorithms can be represented in pseudocode."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633851Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23898-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Pseudocode uses plain language to outline the steps of the algorithm in a logical
  and sequential manner."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633855Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23898-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Pseudocode can be easily understood with only basic knowledge of programming."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633859Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23898-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Pseudocode can be easily translated into different programming languages."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633863Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23914-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "von Neumann architecture is a design of a computer system."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23914-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The von Neumann architecture sends and receives instructions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23914-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The CPU has key components with different characteristics: control unit, arithmetic
  logic unit, buses, registers, clock."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633876Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23914-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The registers in the CPU, each with its own function, are MAR, MDR, CIR, PC,
  Acc."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23902-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Computational thinking can be used to analyse problems and find efficient and
  effective solutions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23902-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Understanding a problem well is key to making sure your solution actually works and
  works efficiently."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23902-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The designer of an algorithm can choose whichever method they feel is most suited to
  the problem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.633892Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23887-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Assembly language is a low-level programming language."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634558Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23887-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It provides direct control over hardware and is used for critical applications and
  embedded systems."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634563Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23918-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Clock speed is measured in gigahertz; 1 gigahertz = 1 billion cycles per second."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634567Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23918-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Increasing the clock speed can increase performance but does depend on other
  components working that fast too."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23918-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Increasing cache size will speed up the device."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634575Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23918-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Increasing cores does not always increase performance."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23896-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An algorithm is a series of defined logical steps that can be followed to solve a
  problem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23896-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A computer program is a way of implementing an algorithm, by writing it in a
  language that a computer can understand."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634587Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23896-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A single algorithm can be implemented in many different computer programs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.634591Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

