# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Misconceptions
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:misconception-linear-search-used-lists-sequences
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A linear search can only be used on lists or sequences of numbers."@en ;
  curric:correction """A linear search can be used on lots of different types of data, including
  strings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.083946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-devices-network-same-thing-send
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """All devices in a network do the same thing, they just send and receive
  data."""@en ;
  curric:correction """In a client–server network, devices have different roles. Servers provide
  services like file storage or email. Clients request and use those services, rather than
  providing them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084426Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-factor-affects-network-performance-fast
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The only factor that affects network performance is how fast your internet
  connection is."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Connection speed does affect performance, but it is also influenced by
  factors like bandwidth, latency, number of users, packet loss, hardware quality and
  interference on wireless networks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084481Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-machine-learning-same-artificial-intelligence
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Machine learning is the same as artificial intelligence."@en ;
  curric:correction """Machine learning is one of the techniques that people can use to build
  artificial intelligence system models. It is a subset of artificial intelligence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084766Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-binary-search-performed-data
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A binary search can be performed on any data."@en ;
  curric:correction """A binary search can only be performed on an ordered list as it finds the
  expected position of the search term based on a selected mid-point in the data."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084772Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-using-low-resoultion-colour-depth
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Using a low resoultion or colour depth for an image makes it unusable."@en ;
  curric:correction """A low resolution or colour depth does not necessarily make an image unusable.
  It depends on the purpose. Lower settings can be suitable for web use, icons or
  thumbnails, while higher quality is needed for printing or detailed graphics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084777Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-network-topologies-work-same-way
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All network topologies work the same way and have the same benefits."@en ;
  curric:correction """Different topologies connect devices in different ways. For example, star
  networks use a central hub, while mesh networks connect devices directly. Each has unique
  strengths and weaknesses depending on the situation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.084993Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-same-text-entered-two-separate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The same text entered into two separate text files will always result in the
  same file size."""@en ;
  curric:correction """How the text has been encoded will affect the file size of a text file. ASCII
  uses 7 bits per character whereas Unicode uses up to 32 bits. Therefore the choice of
  character encoding affects the overall file size of the same text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-classifier-improved-providing-training-data
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A classifier can be improved by providing more training data."@en ;
  curric:correction """More data doesn't always mean improved predictions. The quality of data
  provided to a classifier is as important as the quantity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085599Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-sound-digitised-going-noticeably-different
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Any sound that is digitised is going to be noticeably different to the
  original sound."""@en ;
  curric:correction """When sound is turned into digital form with a high enough sampling rate and
  sample resolution, the difference from the original sound is too small for human ears to
  notice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085604Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-generative-ai-systems-require-training
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Only generative AI systems require training data to complete tasks."@en ;
  curric:correction """All AI systems rely on training data to perform tasks by using patterns
  identified in the data."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.085610Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-penetration-testing-illegal-same-hacking
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Penetration testing is illegal or the same as hacking."@en ;
  curric:correction """Penetration testing is legal and ethical when done with permission. It's a
  form of ethical hacking used to help organisations find and fix security weaknesses before
  real hackers exploit them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086580Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-compression-useful-saving-storage-space
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Compression is only useful for saving storage space."@en ;
  curric:correction """While saving storage is one benefit, compression is also critical for faster
  transmission of files over the internet, reducing bandwidth usage on networks, and
  enabling smooth real-time communication."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.086910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ai-applications-think
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "AI applications can think."@en ;
  curric:correction """AI systems follow programmed rules or improve performance based on data, but
  they do not think or have emotions like humans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087232Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bubble-sort-algorithm-stops-last
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The bubble sort algorithm stops on the last swap."@en ;
  curric:correction """The pass through the list is repeated until no more changes are made on a
  pass. The last pass is needed to confirm the data is in order."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.087244Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-model-improved-providing-training-data
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A model can be improved by providing more training data."@en ;
  curric:correction """Although a large data set is important, more data doesn't necessarily improve
  output. It is important that training data is high-quality, accurate and diverse."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088003Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-students-think-protocols-like-http
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Students may think protocols like HTTP or FTP operate at all layers, or that
  TCP and IP are the only protocols in the model."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Specific protocols perform unique functions at dedicated TCP/IP layers."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088063Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-internet-built-directly-osi-7
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The internet is built directly on the OSI 7-layer model, and its layers are
  actual physical hardware components."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The OSI model is a conceptual framework, not the internet's direct
  architecture. It helps to understand network functions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088120Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-installing-antivirus-software-enough-fully
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Installing antivirus software is enough to fully protect my device from
  malware."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Antivirus software is helpful, but it’s only one part of a broader defence
  strategy. Full protection also requires regular software updates, strong passwords, safe
  browsing habits and user awareness to avoid phishing and suspicious downloads."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.088872Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-technical-jargon-impresses-audience-makes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Technical jargon impresses the audience and makes the presentation better."@en ;
  curric:correction """Presentations should be clear and accessible, using simple language and
  examples that everyone can understand."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089023Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-huffman-tree-compressed-file
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The Huffman tree is the compressed file."@en ;
  curric:correction """The compressed file is a sequence of bits, and the tree is the representation
  of the coding system."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089343Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-world-wide-web-single-entity
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The World Wide Web is a single entity stored in one place."@en ;
  curric:correction """The World Wide Web is a vast collection of interconnected websites and
  documents hosted on servers all over the world. Your web browser accesses these different
  locations to display the information you see."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089405Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bits-bytes-same-thing-refer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Bits and bytes are the same thing. They all refer to binary numbers."@en ;
  curric:correction """A bit is the smallest unit of data. A byte is a group of 8 bits and is used
  to summarise larger sequences of bits in a more convenient way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089609Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-devices-network-share-same-mac
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """All devices on a network share the same MAC address because they’re connected
  to the same router."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Each network device has its own unique MAC address assigned to its network
  interface card (NIC)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089617Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-wired-networks-use-same-type
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All wired networks use the same type of cable."@en ;
  curric:correction """Copper Ethernet and fibre optic cables have different speeds, distances and
  uses. For example, copper Ethernet is fine for short distances, but fibre optic is better
  for fast, long-distance connections."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.089623Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bubble-sort-fast-efficient-sorting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Bubble sort is a fast and efficient sorting algorithm."@en ;
  curric:correction """Bubble sort is considered inefficient for large data sets, but it can be made
  more efficient by using a flag to indicate when a swap is made in a single pass."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-insertion-sort-slower-other-sorting
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "An insertion sort is slower than other sorting algorithms."@en ;
  curric:correction """While other algorithms offer better time complexity for large, unsorted
  arrays, insertion sort can still be faster in practice for smaller and partially sorted
  lists."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.090708Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-compression-useful-pictures-photos
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Compression is only useful for pictures or photos."@en ;
  curric:correction """Compression applies to many types of files such as MP3 for audio, MP4 for
  video, ZIP for grouped files."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-binary-used-represent-numerical-data
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Binary is only used to represent numerical data."@en ;
  curric:correction """Binary digits can be used to form sequences that can be used to represent any
  data. As long as it is identified what each sequence represents, binary digits can become
  any form of data or instructions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091390Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-sample-rate-resolution-samples-adjusts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The sample rate and resolution of samples adjusts based on the sound that is
  being digitsed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The digitsation of sound needs to be consistent so that the binary sequence
  represented can be processed as expected."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091395Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-best-compression-method-one-makes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The best compression method is the one that makes files the smallest."@en ;
  curric:correction """Smaller isn’t always better, sometimes important details are lost. The best
  method depends on the file type, quality needs, and purpose."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091599Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-neural-networks-offer-transparency-terms
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Neural networks offer transparency in terms of the decisions made by the
  algorithm."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It’s often hard to understand why a neural network made a particular decision
  which makes transparency difficult."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091607Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-default-decimal-addition-fact
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils will often default to decimal addition, in the fact that 1+1 = 2,
  whereas in binary 1+1 = 10."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind students that binary only has two digits; 0 and 1. Use the comparisons
  between binary and decimal addition in the slide deck to illustrate the differences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091613Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-networks-server-because-server-needed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """All networks must have a server because a server is always needed to share
  files or printers between devices."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Not all networks need a server. In a peer-to-peer model, each computer can
  act as both client and server, sharing files directly. This setup is simpler but may lack
  central control and security."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091619Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bitmap-images-large-screen-poor
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Bitmap images that are large on screen are always poor quality."@en ;
  curric:correction """The quality of a bitmap image depends on its resolution, not just its size on
  the screen. A high-resolution bitmap can appear sharp and detailed, while a low-resolution
  bitmap may look pixelated when enlarged."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091625Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-higher-compression-ratio-means-better
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A higher compression ratio always means better quality."@en ;
  curric:correction """A higher compression ratio actually means the file size has been reduced
  more. This often results in lower quality, especially with lossy compression."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091774Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-linear-search-algorithm-binary-search
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A linear search algorithm and binary search algorithm are equally complex to
  write."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Binary search algorithms are more complex to write due to the different paths
  that the algorithm can take rather than stepping through the search data in order."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-merge-sort-efficient-sorting-algorithm
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Merge sort is the most efficient sorting algorithm for all cases."@en ;
  curric:correction """For smaller data sets, simpler algorithms such as insertion sort or bubble
  sort can be faster due to the overhead in merge sort of having to break apart the data to
  be sorted."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.091785Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-performing-binary-multiplication-result-stored
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When performing binary multiplication any result can be stored, regardless of
  how many binary digits are needed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The size of a binary number that can be stored is allocated in memory.
  Sometimes the result of a binary shift may result in a larger binary number that can be
  stored in the number of bits available."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092085Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-convert-8-bit-binary-number
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You have to convert an 8 bit binary number in one go."@en ;
  curric:correction """As a hexadecimal digit can be represented by 4 binary digits, it is useful to
  convert binary numbers in nibbles (4-bits at a time). This way each digit can be converted
  separately and then recombined for the final value."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092090Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-wireless-networks-better-wired-ones
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Wireless networks are always better than wired ones because they don’t use
  cables."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Wireless is more convenient, but it can be slower, less secure and more prone
  to interference. Wired connections are often better for speed, stability and data heavy
  tasks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092354Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ai-think-make-decisions-like
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "AI can think and make decisions like humans."@en ;
  curric:correction """AI systems have no awareness or emotions and do not think or understand in
  the way humans do. AI systems process data and follow patterns or rules based on training
  data."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092453Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-hexadecimal-numbers-used-take-less
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Hexadecimal numbers are used to take up less memory on the computer."@en ;
  curric:correction """Computers still only process and store binary data. Hexadecimal is used by
  humans to help them process long binary sequences more easily but the underlying number of
  bits is still the same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092459Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-computers-use-binary-data-instructions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Computers use binary for data and instructions but they can use other number
  systems just as easily."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Computers have to use binary as they are powered by electrical circuits which
  contain transistors which can be switched on and off using electricity. Using other number
  systems would require more complex circuitry."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092529Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-think-place-value-binary
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils may think the place value for binary is the same as decimal in the fact
  each place value to the left is 10 times greater."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Binary place values double. So the first bit has the place value of 1 and the
  second has the place value of 2 and so on."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092629Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-supervised-learning-model-stores-memorises
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """In supervised learning, the model stores or \"memorises\" the training data to
  label new, unprocessed data."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A supervised learning model does not simply store or \"memorise\" training
  data. It detects patterns and relationships in the training data and stores these. If it
  only stored the training data, it could not accurately label new, unprocessed data."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092827Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ascii-unicode-used-represent-characters
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """ASCII and Unicode are only used to represent the characters and symbols found
  in written communication across all languages in the world."""@en ;
  curric:correction """ASCII and Unicode include more than just characters from written languages.
  ASCII represents English letters, numbers and symbols. Unicode supports other symbols
  beyond written text, including mathematical symbols, emojis and non-text elements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092969Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-lossy-compression-results-poor-quality
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Lossy compression always results in a poor quality file that is not as usable
  as the original version."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Lossy compression removes data that is considered unnecessary or less
  noticeable, which may not impact the perceived quality of the file, especially to the
  human eye or ear."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.092981Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-sample-rate-bit-depth-samples
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The sample rate and bit depth of samples adjusts based on the sound that is
  being digitsed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The digitsation of sound needs to be consistent so that the binary sequence
  represented can be processed as expected."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093068Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-learners-think-inner-loop-runs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Learners may think that the inner loop only runs once per program, rather than
  repeating fully each time the outer loop runs."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The inner loop runs completely every time the outer loop runs once. This
  means the code inside the inner loop is repeated multiple times depending on how many
  times the outer loop is executed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093393Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-order-instructions-program-doesnt-really
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The order of instructions in a program doesn't really matter, as long as all
  the instructions are there."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Computers execute code line by line, in the order it's written. If you change
  the sequence, you're changing the steps the computer takes, and that will change the
  output."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093399Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-network-failure-means-internet-stops
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Network failure just means the internet stops working for a bit; it’s annoying
  but not serious."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Network failure can lead to data loss, financial damage and safety risks in
  sectors like healthcare. It is more than just an inconvenience and can impact lives and
  businesses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.093607Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ai-systems-improve-access-digital
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "AI systems improve access to digital technologies."@en ;
  curric:correction """Inequality of access to AI tools and systems is an ethical concern. Not
  everyone has equal access to AI tools which can actually increase the digital divide."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094061Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-way-store-multiple-records-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "There is no way to store multiple records in one data structure in Python."@en ;
  curric:correction """If you want to use multiple records in a database, then you can add multiple
  dictionaries to a list."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-logical-expression-check-one-value
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A logical expression can only check one value."@en ;
  curric:correction """Logical expressions can combine relational and logical operators to check
  multiple values or inputs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094212Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-operator-used-comparison
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The = operator is used for comparison."@en ;
  curric:correction """When using Python for programming the == operator is used for comparison and
  the = operator is used for assignment. Other languages may not always use these operators
  for these tasks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094729Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pans-limited-bluetooth-wi-fi
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "PANs are limited to Bluetooth or Wi-Fi connections."@en ;
  curric:correction """PANs can use a variety of technologies, including wired connections like USB
  and FireWire, and wireless connections like Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, and more."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094791Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-sensor-follows-line-like-smart
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The sensor follows the line like a smart camera."@en ;
  curric:correction """The sensor sends data back to the microcontroller to say whether light or
  dark is detected. The written code uses this data to decide how the buggy should respond."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094802Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-your-data-sorted-cannot-use
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "If your data is not sorted then you cannot use a binary search."@en ;
  curric:correction """Data does need to be sorted to use a binary search, though use of a sorting
  algorithm first would allow binary search to be used. However, consideration must be given
  as to the benefit of this approach for searching."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094821Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-run-length-encoding-reduces-file
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Run length encoding always reduces file size."@en ;
  curric:correction """Run length encoding only works well when data has long repeated patterns. If
  data is random or has frequent changes, RLE may not reduce the file size and can even make
  it bigger. For example, compressing \"HELLO\" with RLE results in \"1H1E2L1O\"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.094831Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-javascript-works-everything-perfect-ill
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """JavaScript only works after everything is perfect, I’ll fix it all at
  the end."""@en ;
  curric:correction """JavaScript is best written and tested in small steps. Writing a little,
  testing it, and debugging as you go helps avoid big problems later."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095068Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-metadata-used-user-needs-know
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Metadata is only used when a user needs to know when a file was made or
  changed."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Metadata can be used in a variety of ways. For example, software can be
  designed to make use of metadata for effective cataloguing and providing extra information
  about the properites of a file being used."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095239Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-someone-cannot-view-image-web
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """If someone cannot view an image on a web page it can be ignored as text on the
  page will be sufficient."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Images are used in web pages to provide the reader with extra context. By not
  describing them in some way the reader might not understand the information in the same
  way than if it was viewed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095548Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-indexing-starts-1-location-first
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Indexing starts at 1 as that is the location of the first element."@en ;
  curric:correction "In Python, and many other programming languages, indexing starts at 0."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.095553Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-possible-interrogate-csv-file-python
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """It is not possible to interrogate a CSV file in Python without importing a
  specialised library."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A CSV file behaves in the same way as a txt file in Python. Data is read from
  the file as strings and methods can be used to remove extra characters like commas,
  spliting the values either side in to separate items."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096046Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-large-language-models-llms-understand
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Large Language Models (LLMs) understand what they’re saying, like a human
  does."""@en ;
  curric:correction """LLMs do not understand language or meaning. They generate responses by
  predicting the most likely next word based on patterns in the data they were trained on,
  not because they understand the content like a human does."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096089Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-spreadsheet-formatting-used-make-spreadsheet
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Spreadsheet formatting is only used to make a spreadsheet look attractive."@en ;
  curric:correction """Spreadsheet formatting is used to make information clearer but is also
  important to ensure data values such as currency are formatted correctly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.096836Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-learners-think-loop-repeat-forever
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Learners may think a for loop will always repeat forever unless they manually
  stop it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A for loop repeats a set number of times, based on the range or count value
  given. The loop ends automatically when the final value in the range has been reached."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097136Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-boolean-logic-used-logic-circuits
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Boolean logic is only used in logic circuits and logic gates."@en ;
  curric:correction """The three fundamental Boolean operators are AND, OR and NOT. These are used
  in programs to perform selection and control program flow. In Python, these are written in
  words as: and, or, not."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097142Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-function-ever-return-one-value
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A function can only ever return one value."@en ;
  curric:correction "A list can be used to return multiple values from a function."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097150Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-microcontroller-controls-systems-same-time
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The microcontroller controls all systems at the same time."@en ;
  curric:correction """In reality, most microcontrollers execute code sequentially, one line at a
  time. It may appear that microcontrollers are doing many things at once, but they’re
  actually switching between tasks quickly or handling them step by step."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097614Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-python-built-xor-operator-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Python has a built-in XOR operator in the same way that it has AND, OR and
  NOT."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Unlike AND, OR and NOT, Python does not have a built-in operator for XOR and
  instead must be designed as part of and program that uses it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.097760Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-function-procedure-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A function and a procedure are the same."@en ;
  curric:correction """A function is different from a procedure because it returns a value or values
  to the main program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098329Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-social-engineering-involves-technical-hacking
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Social engineering only involves technical hacking or complex
  cyberattacks."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Social engineering mainly targets human psychology, not technical
  vulnerabilities. It's more about exploiting trust and human error than technical skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-network-security-stops-viruses-its
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Network security just stops viruses, so it’s only important for large
  organisations, not for individuals or small businesses."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Network security protects all users, not just large organisations. It
  prevents data theft, fraud, and service disruption. Individuals need protection from
  threats like phishing or ransomware."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098836Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-physical-computing-programming-robots
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Physical computing is just about programming robots."@en ;
  curric:correction """Physical computing is much broader than just robotics. It includes any system
  where a computer interacts with the physical world through sensors and actuators, for
  example wearable devices, environmental sensors and smart home devices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.098978Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-big-data-stored-normal-data
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Big data can be stored in normal data strcutures like relational
  databases."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Big data is mostly unstructured, so it doesn't fit the row-and-column format
  of relational databases."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099213Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-data-website-travels-together-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """All the data from a website travels together in one file and always takes the
  same route through the internet to reach your device."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Data is broken into packets, and each packet may take a different route. This
  makes transmission faster and more reliable, because the network can avoid delays or busy
  routes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099308Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dont-need-hardware-cloud-everything
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You don’t need any hardware for the cloud — everything just happens
  online."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The cloud still relies on physical hardware, like servers, storage devices
  and networking equipment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099465Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-search-engines-instantly-know-website
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Search engines instantly know every website and search live each time you type
  in a query."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Search engines don’t search the web in real time. They use crawlers to index
  content in advance. When you search, they quickly scan this index to return the most
  relevant results."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-because-data-stored-cloud-doesnt
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Because data is stored in the cloud, it doesn’t have a physical or
  environmental impact."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The term \"cloud\" sounds invisible, so many people assume their photos,
  videos and files are floating around in some harmless digital space. But in reality the
  cloud is made up of millions of physical data centres which are based across the world."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-macro-used-clear-data-spreadsheet
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A macro can only be used to clear data in a spreadsheet."@en ;
  curric:correction """A macro is used to record and repeat tasks that can be automated in a
  spreadsheet. They are not just used to clear or reset data."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099681Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-countif-function-same-count-function
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The COUNTIF function is the same as the COUNT function."@en ;
  curric:correction """A COUNTIF function returns the total number of cells based on a set
  criterion, whereas the COUNT function returns the number of cells that contain a number in
  a range."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-input-wired-one-logic-gate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Each input can only be wired to one logic gate."@en ;
  curric:correction """Logic gates can be combined to create complex circuits that represent any
  number of logic statements combined. This can involve the same input being connected to
  multiple logic gates."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099695Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-modern-technology-improved-individuals-working
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Modern technology has improved individuals' working lives in all aspects."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are some negative impacts of modern-day technology on the workplace and
  individual workers. These include fewer opportunities for face-to-face communication and
  24/7 connectivity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.099701Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-primary-key-foreign-key-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A primary key and a foreign key are the same thing."@en ;
  curric:correction """A primary key is an attribute that uniquely identifies a record in a database
  table, whereas a foreign key is an attribute in one table that is the primary key in
  another table and is used to link the tables together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101068Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-testing-making-sure-program-runs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Testing is just about making sure the program runs."@en ;
  curric:correction """It's not just about running the program. We test to make sure the program
  does exactly what it's supposed to do, in all situations. This means checking if it
  handles correct input and incorrect input correctly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101320Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-write-integers-directly-csv-file
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You can write integers directly to a CSV file using file.write(number)."@en ;
  curric:correction "All data must be converted to strings before writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101328Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-adding-features-makes-product-better
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Adding more features always makes a product better."@en ;
  curric:correction """Adding features should be done carefully, focusing on usefulness and how well
  they work together to solve a problem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101334Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-communication-workplace-same-communication-family
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Communication in the workplace is the same as communication with family or
  friends."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Communication in the workplace should be formal and professional. Slang
  language, abbreviations and emojis should be avoided."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101650Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cannot-protect-your-online-reputation
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You cannot protect your online reputation."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are many ways that you can protect your online reputation. The main way
  to do this is ensure you think about what you put online in the first place in the same
  way as you present yourself in real life."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101692Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-feasibility-report-outlines-key-requirements
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A feasibility report outlines the key requirements of a system."@en ;
  curric:correction """A feasibility report is a document used in project management that assesses
  whether a project can be completed successfully."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101706Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-malware-affects-computers-phones-tablets
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Malware only affects computers, not phones or tablets."@en ;
  curric:correction """Malware can infect any idevice that is connected to the internet, including
  smartphones, tablets and smart TVs. Mobile malware is increasingly common and can steal
  data, track location or lock users out of their devices — just like on computers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101892Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-network-threats-attacks-come-external
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Network threats and attacks come only from external hackers or from sources
  outside a network, while internal users or trusted software pose no risk."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Threats can be internal, like careless employees or malicious insiders, as
  well as external."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.101906Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dbms-used-storing-data
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A DBMS is only used for storing data."@en ;
  curric:correction """While storage is a major function, a DBMS also provides data security,
  integrity and querying capabilities."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102304Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-fake-news-easy-spot-because
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Fake news is easy to spot because it’s obviously false or silly."@en ;
  curric:correction """Fake news is often designed to look real and believable. It can mimic trusted
  sources, use partial truths, or appeal to emotions to trick people. It’s important to
  check information sources and think critically, even if a post seems convincing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102310Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-gantt-charts-effective-kanban-boards
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Gantt charts are more effective than Kanban boards because they show project
  dependencies."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Neither tool can be deemed more effective overall. A business should decide
  which of the tools will work well for them based on the needs of the project."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102660Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-comments-added-code-help-understand
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Comments are added to code to help you understand your program."@en ;
  curric:correction """Comments are used to make the code more readable to a programmer who seeks to
  understand it. The comments should be written in a style that would help them make sense
  of the program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102830Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-exception-handling-fixes-error-code
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Exception handling fixes the error in the code or stops it from happening."@en ;
  curric:correction """Exception handling does not prevent errors but allows the program to detect
  them and continue running by managing the error appropriately."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102836Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-program-logic-error-work-give
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """If a program has a logic error it will not work and will give error
  messages."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Logic errors are errors that cause a program to work incorrectly or
  unexpectedly. With a logic error, the program can be run without failing, but it does not
  return the expected result. The user might not realise that there is an error."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102842Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-program-automatically-ask-people-try
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A program will automatically ask people to try again if data is invalid."@en ;
  curric:correction """The program will only ask for data to be input again if it has been
  programmed to do so; otherwise it will run with invalid data and may crash."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102847Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-two-people-type-same-search
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When two people type in the same search term into a search engine, they will
  get the same results."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Two people could search the same term online, but based on their search
  history, they could receive very different results."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.102858Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cybersecurity-jobs-highly-technical-people
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Cybersecurity jobs are only for highly technical people who know how to code
  or hack."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Cybersecurity careers are diverse, and many roles value communication,
  analytical thinking, problem solving and ethical judgment just as much as technical
  skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103232Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-encryption-makes-data-completely-safe
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Encryption makes data completely safe and unbreakable."@en ;
  curric:correction """Encryption greatly improves security, but it is not foolproof. If encryption
  keys are weak, stolen or mismanaged, encrypted data can still be accessed by attackers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103237Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-delivering-presentation-read-slides-word
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When delivering a presentation you should read the slides out word for
  word."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Simply reading out the slides can disengage the audience and mean that your
  message can become lost."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103468Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-function-return-words-true-false
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The IF function can only return the words True or False to the user."@en ;
  curric:correction """The IF function returns a result of True or False, but you can set what
  message will be displayed to the user for each result within the function."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103474Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-text-file-stored-anywhere-used
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A text file can be stored anywhere to be used in a program using just the file
  name."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A text file must be stored in the same location as a program to be used to be
  accessed by file name alone. If it is stored elsewhere, the full path of the file will
  also need to be included."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103479Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ciphers-encryption-same-thing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Ciphers and encryption are the same thing."@en ;
  curric:correction """Ciphers are one type of encryption method. Encryption includes ciphers but
  also involves algorithms, keys, and protocols used in modern digital security systems."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.103878Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ultrasonic-sensors-work-like-cameras
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Ultrasonic sensors work like cameras and detect objects visually."@en ;
  curric:correction "Ultrasonic sensors use sound not light to detect objects."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.104597Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-hackers-criminals-trying-steal-destroy
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All hackers are criminals trying to steal or destroy data."@en ;
  curric:correction """Not all hackers are malicious. There are different types of hackers such as
  white hat ethical hackers, grey hat hackers who may break rules but not for personal gain
  and black hat hackers who are malicious hackers who exploit systems illegally."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105032Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-write-full-code-random-number
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You have to write the full code for random number generation yourself."@en ;
  curric:correction """Python's standard library includes the random module, which already has
  functions like randint() to generate random numbers. You just need to import it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105553Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-spreadsheet-used-explore-costs-event
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A spreadsheet can only be used to explore the costs of the event after it has
  happened."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A spreadsheet model can be used to predict and model the costs of the event
  before it happens to help the organisers make decisions about income and expenditure."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.105560Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-sql-statements-used-exisiting-tables
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "SQL statements can only be used with exisiting tables."@en ;
  curric:correction """SQL statements can be used to perform other actions on a databse such as
  creating new tables."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106231Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-type-chart-select-doesnt-matter
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The type of chart you select doesn't matter, all charts will represent data
  effectively."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Different types of chart present different types of data effectively. For
  example, a pie chart is used to represent data that makes up a whole part or 100%."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106835Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-nested-selection-statement-one-nested
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A nested selection statement can only have one nested selection block."@en ;
  curric:correction """Selection statements can can continue to be nested in further selection
  blocks to provide more complex conditions for which specific code will be executed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106941Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-start-coding-figure-go-planning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """I can just start coding and figure it out as I go. Planning is a waste of time
  and boring."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Planning is like building a strong foundation. A good plan helps you write
  better code faster."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106961Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cpu-decodes-understands-instructions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The CPU decodes and understands the instructions."@en ;
  curric:correction """The instruction is decoded and then executed. The process only executes the
  instructions received."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.106994Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-random-module-generate-random-numbers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The random module will only generate random numbers."@en ;
  curric:correction "The random module can generate random characters as well as numbers."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107690Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-long-necessary-lines-code-present
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As long as all the necessary lines of code are present, the program will work,
  regardless of their order."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Computers run code line by line, in the order it's written. If you change the
  sequence, you're changing the steps the computer takes, and that will change the output."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.107753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-conditional-formatting-needs-applied-time
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Conditional formatting needs to be applied each time a value in a cell
  changes."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Conditional formatting will automatically update if the value in a cell
  changes, as soon as a value meets the condition, the formatting will be appplied."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108167Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-using-select-best-method-returning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Using SELECT * is always the best method for returning data from a database
  table."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You should only use the SELECT * query when all fields are needed. Including
  unnecessary data can be frustrating for the person viewing and working with the results."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108173Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-project-brief-includes-success-criteria
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A project brief always includes success criteria."@en ;
  curric:correction """Sometimes a project brief may not include success criteria, but a brief
  description of what the program needs to do. You may need to generate success criteria
  from the project brief."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108201Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-javascript-changes-original-html-file
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "JavaScript changes the original HTML file."@en ;
  curric:correction """JavaScript only changes what the user sees in the browser. It does not change
  the actual HTML file saved on your computer or server."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108206Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-once-program-developed-finished-need
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Once a program has been developed, it is finished and there is no need to
  evaluate or reflect on what you have done."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Evaluation is about judging how well the program meets the original success
  criteria or requirements. It can help you to revisit and make improvements to a program,
  as well as reflect on lessons learnt for your next project."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108355Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-proprietary-software-costs-money
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Proprietary software always costs money."@en ;
  curric:correction """Proprietary software is usually sold to end users, although sometimes it is
  available for free."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.108603Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ai-image-generators-create-completely
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "AI image generators create completely original artwork from scratch."@en ;
  curric:correction """AI image generators create new images by learning from and combining patterns
  found in millions of existing images. They don’t “imagine” or invent things like a human
  artist; they remix data they were trained on."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110130Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dont-need-wireframe-site-map
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "I don’t need a wireframe or site map, I can just start coding."@en ;
  curric:correction """Planning is a key step in web development. A wireframe helps you decide where
  things go before writing any code, and a site map ensures you know how pages connect.
  Skipping planning often leads to messy code and confusing navigation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.110298Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cannot-print-game-board-table
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You cannot print a game board or table layout neatly in Python."@en ;
  curric:correction "You can added spaces and | to format a game board or table in Python."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112094Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-use-planning-tools-gantt-pert
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You should use all planning tools (Gantt, PERT and feasibility reports)."@en ;
  curric:correction """You don't need to use all planning tools; select the tools most suitable for
  a project."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112116Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-copyright-applies-use-images
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Copyright only applies to the use of images."@en ;
  curric:correction "Copyright refers to any creation by an original creator."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-testing-done-end-project
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Testing should only be done at the end of a project."@en ;
  curric:correction "It is good practice to test products during and at the end of a project."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112472Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-html-programming-language
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "HTML is a programming language."@en ;
  curric:correction """HTML is a markup language. It defines the structure and appearance of content
  on a web page, but does not not do any processing of data into information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.112995Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-physical-sense-hat-device-practice
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You must have the physical Sense HAT device to practice coding with the Sense
  HAT."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You do not have to have the physical Sense HAT to try this out. The Sense HAT
  emulator provides a digital representation of the device."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113007Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-append-method-replace-existing-contents
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The append() method will replace the existing contents of a list."@en ;
  curric:correction """The append() method will add an item to the end of an existing list but it
  will not replace or overwrite any existing items in a list."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113022Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-list-static-once-created-cannot
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A list is static, so once it is created it cannot be edited or amended."@en ;
  curric:correction """A list is a dynamic data structure that can change in size. The append()
  function can be used to add elements to a list."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113330Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-define-constant-programming-language
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You can define a constant in any programming language."@en ;
  curric:correction """Python does not have constants. But if you want a value to be treated as a
  constant, it's a common naming convention for the identifier to be written in capital
  letters."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113385Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-input-output-program-happen-automatically
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Input and output of a program happen automatically, without the need for
  coding. The computer uses it in the correct part of your program."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Computers process instructions in code that requires input and output. The
  programmer needs to specify exactly where and how it should be handled."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113405Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-parts-solution-coded-same-time
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """All parts of a solution must be coded at the same time and tested that it
  works once coding has finished."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Individual subproblems can be approached separately and tested to ensure they
  work before moving onto the next part. It helps to know parts of a program work as
  intended."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113419Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-formulas-used-cells-within-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Formulas can only be used on cells within one worksheet in a spreadsheet."@en ;
  curric:correction "Formulas can work across multiple worksheets in a spreadsheet."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113621Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-system-tested-normal-data-expected
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A system should only be tested with normal data that will be expected. If it
  works with normal data it will work all the time."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A system should be tested with a range of test data, including erroneous data
  that is not meant to be accepted. Programs should make sure that there is no way to stop
  the software from working if invalid inputs are entered."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113626Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dont-need-follow-project-brief
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "I don’t need to follow the project brief to draw a flowchart."@en ;
  curric:correction """The project brief gives you the purpose and requirements of the program. A
  flowchart must reflect those to show how the program will work step by step."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113632Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-finished-code-runs-dont-need
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "I finished the code and it runs, so I don’t need to test it."@en ;
  curric:correction """Just because a program runs doesn’t mean it works correctly in all
  situations. Testing helps find hidden errors, especially with unusual or unexpected inputs
  that you might not think of."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-threats-online-illegal
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All threats online are illegal."@en ;
  curric:correction """Not all threats are illegal, some threats do not break laws but can cause
  harm."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.113761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pseudocode-same-programming-language-follow
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pseudocode is the same as a programming language and must follow a particular
  syntax."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Pseudocode is independent of a specific programming language and does not
  need to follow any particular rules. All that is required is that a programmer can read
  the pseudocode and understand how to implement it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114069Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-loop-run-least-once
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A loop will always run at least once."@en ;
  curric:correction """A loop only runs if the condition allows it. If the condition isn’t met
  initially, the code inside won’t run at all."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114200Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-test-plan-include-data-cause
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A test plan should only include data that will cause a program to not
  work."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A test plan should contain a range of test data, including normal, erroneous
  and boundary."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114205Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-one-correct-solution-problem-programming
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "There is only one correct solution to a problem when programming."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are lots of different approaches to solving a problem in programming.
  Some solutions can work better than others but the first stage in getting a solution is
  ensuring that it provides the expected outputs that are required."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114219Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-once-product-completed-need-improved
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Once a product is completed it does not need to be improved if I am happy with
  it as the creator."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Listening to other opinions and referring to the success criteria of the
  client brief is essential to help develop a product that meets the client brief
  completely."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.114758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ml-models-neutral-give-fair
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "ML models are neutral and always give fair or accurate information."@en ;
  curric:correction """ML models can reflect or amplify bias in their training data. If the data
  contains stereotypes or imbalances, the ML model can repeat or reinforce them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115685Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-function-returns-value-used-throughout
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """When a function returns a value it can be used throughout the program that
  called it."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The return value needs to be stored if it is to be used later in the program
  that calls it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.115748Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-supporting-employees-mental-physical-wellbeing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Supporting an employee's mental or physical wellbeing only costs an
  organisation."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Supporting an employee's mental or physical wellbeing can actually benefit an
  organisation through reduced time off and increased productivity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116574Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-once-ai-built-cant-changed
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Once AI is built, it can’t be changed and the risks are already set."@en ;
  curric:correction """AI systems can and should be continuously monitored, tested and improved to
  reduce risks. Risk mitigation is an ongoing process, not a one-time fix."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.116587Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-program-run-line-line-top
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A program must run line by line from top to bottom."@en ;
  curric:correction """A subrotuine is an 'out of line' block of code, which is typcially written at
  the top of a program and then called upon within the main program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117447Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-long-components-attached-buggy-work
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "As long as the components are attached the buggy will work fine."@en ;
  curric:correction """A good chassis design isn’t just about holding parts. Care should be taken
  when positioning and securing components to ensure the buggy is reliable, easy to fix and
  functions as intended."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.117916Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-working-collaboratively-positive-impact-productivity
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Working collaboratively is always positive and has an impact on
  productivity."""@en ;
  curric:correction """There are some disadvantages to collaborative working, for example complex
  decision making with multiple people can become a lengthy process and coordination of
  resources can be difficult."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.118075Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-project-management-alter-outcome-project
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Project management will not alter the outcome of a project or make it a
  success."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Project management will not guarantee success of a project, but effective
  project management will increase the likelihood of a project being successful."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119235Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-generative-ai-systems-output-accurate
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Generative AI systems output is always accurate and based on facts."@en ;
  curric:correction """Generative AI systems can produce convincing text but the output is not
  always accurate or based on facts. Fact checking is always important because AI systems
  generate content based on patterns in the training data, not verified information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.119873Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-interaction-occur-consecutive-stages-project
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Interaction can only occur between consecutive stages of the project
  lifecycle."""@en ;
  curric:correction "Interaction can happen across multiple stages of the project lifecycle."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.120379Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-assigning-variable-inside-function-automatically
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Assigning a variable inside a function automatically makes it global."@en ;
  curric:correction "A variable is local, unless it is specifically set as a global variable."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122754Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-synchronous-communication-tools-better-asynchronous
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Synchronous communication tools are better than asynchronous communication
  tools."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Neither type of communication can be deemed better than the other overall.
  Some forms of communication will suit different tasks better than others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122770Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-deepfakes-easy-spot-because-look
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Deepfakes are easy to spot because they always look fake or glitchy"@en ;
  curric:correction """Many deepfakes today are highly realistic and difficult to detect, especially
  when viewed quickly or shared on social media. As technology improves, deepfakes can mimic
  real people’s voices and faces with convincing detail."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122799Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-arrays-lists-behave-same-way
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Arrays and lists behave in the same way."@en ;
  curric:correction """An array has a predefined fixed size. A list can vary in size throughout
  program execution."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122827Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dictionary-static-data-structure-meaning
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A dictionary is a static data structure meaning you cannot add or remove
  items, only change the values that are available."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A dictionary is a dynamic data structure, which means you can add or remove
  items in the data structure during program execution."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.122870Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-matter-camera-positioned-long-action
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """It does not matter how the camera is positioned as long as the action is
  captured."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The camera angle can help portray a key element of the moment to the viewer
  and help them understand the meaning of the clip."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.123242Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-web-page-divisions-need-unique
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Web page divisions all need to have unique labels. They can't be the same."@en ;
  curric:correction """When designing divisions of a web page the same formatting may need to be
  applied to multiple divisions. In this case the labels would need to be the same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124236Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-fill-handle-used-replicate-formulas
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The fill handle can only be used to replicate formulas."@en ;
  curric:correction "The fill handle can replicate formulas, text and numbers."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124247Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cannot-protect-yourself-against-content
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You cannot protect yourself against the content you see online."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are number of steps you can take to reduce the likelihood of seeing
  unwanted content online, these include using safe search tools, only streaming content
  legally and on a secure connection and using privacy-preserving search engines."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124450Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-operations-programs-performed-numbers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Operations in programs can only be performed on numbers."@en ;
  curric:correction """Operations can be performed on different types of data. What the operator
  does can change depending on the data type it is being used with."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124600Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-program-follows-sequence-instructions-run
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A program follows a sequence of instructions and will run all lines of
  code."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Selection statements can be used to control program flow, so some lines of
  code can be skipped to follow a different path through the program."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124622Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-condition-while-loop-checked-once
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The condition in a while loop is only checked once. The loop will always run a
  fixed number of times."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind students that the condition is checked before each iteration. The loop
  repeats only while the condition is True. Variable changes inside the loop affect whether
  it continues or stops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.124628Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-like-addition-subtraction-multiplication-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Just like addition, subtraction and multiplication there is only one type of
  division in programming."""@en ;
  curric:correction """There are three types of division in programming; real, integer and modulo
  division. Each deal with remainder values differently and will be useful in different ways
  in programming."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125259Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-delete-data-database-using-sql
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You can delete data from a database using an SQL command without any
  consideration."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You should delete data using SQL commands carefully as data may be linked to
  other tables in the database."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.125821Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-specific-laws-designed-online-crimes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "There are specific laws that are designed for online crimes."@en ;
  curric:correction """In the UK, we don’t currently have one law that decides what is and is not
  illegal online. Instead something is illegal if it is illegal offline or is included as an
  offence in one of many pieces of legislation that govern the internet in the UK."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126081Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-information-www-accessed-anyone-world
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "If information is on the WWW, it can be accessed by anyone in the world."@en ;
  curric:correction """Governments in different countries restrict what can be viewed or published
  by the citizens within their country."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.126087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-project-brief-set-way-solve
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A project brief is a set way to solve a problem."@en ;
  curric:correction """A project brief outlines the requirements of a system, but there may be many
  ways to solve the problem. The brief explains what needs to be solved, not how."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127052Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-boolean-logic-statements-processed-order
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Boolean logic statements should be processed in the order they are read (from
  left to right)."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Boolean operators have an order of precedence that affects the which operator
  applies to which variable. If a different order is required, brackets should be used."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.127407Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-type-anything-llm-give-best
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You can just type anything into an LLM and it will always give the best
  answer."""@en ;
  curric:correction """LLMs work best when you give them clear, specific and well-structured
  prompts. The quality of the input directly affects the quality of the output; this process
  of designing and refining inputs to get better results is called prompt engineering."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.130406Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-functions-procedures-different-names-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Functions and procedures are just different names for the same thing."@en ;
  curric:correction """A function is a type of subroutine that returns a value whereas a procedure
  is a type of subroutine that does not return a value."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.131922Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-users-dont-ever-see-underlying
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Users don't ever see the underlying file structure of a website, so it's
  organisation is unimportant."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Organisation of resources can make the creation and maintainence of websites
  an easier task. The quicker a developer of website can find the component parts, the less
  time will be wasted when changes need to be made."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-easier-apply-css-directly-html
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "It is easier to apply CSS directly to the HTML tags as they are used."@en ;
  curric:correction """There is little time saved by applying CSS directly to tags and it generates
  more work later if the same changes need to be made in different parts of a web page."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.132879Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-poster-created-using-software-digital
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A poster that is created using software is digital even when printed out."@en ;
  curric:correction """The source of the design is digital if it was created using software.
  However, once that digital design is printed onto a physical medium like paper, the
  resulting poster itself becomes a physical artefact."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-lifecycle-plan-follow-start-finish
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The lifecycle is a plan you follow from start to finish in sequence."@en ;
  curric:correction """Once you get to the testing and evaluation stage, you may move back to the
  execution stage until you are happy with the product."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134686Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-data-validation-check-values-entered
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Data validation can only check values entered into a cell. It cannot be used
  to stop a user from leaving a cell blank."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Data validation can be used to prevent users from leaving required cells
  blank."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.134972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-gantt-charts-better-pert-charts
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Gantt charts are better than PERT charts."@en ;
  curric:correction """Gantt charts may be deemed better than PERT charts in some instances, but not
  all. The choice of chart can depend on the project and what the team prefers to use."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.136966Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-websites-require-specialist-knowledge-create
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Websites require specialist knowledge to create and publish."@en ;
  curric:correction """Drag-and-drop software and online platforms allow anyone to create and
  publish a website easily."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.137563Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-storage-means-faster-computer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "More storage always means a faster computer."@en ;
  curric:correction """Upgrading from a HDD to a SSD will improve speed, but simply increasing the
  capacity of the same type of drive does not make the computer faster."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138606Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pupils-find-difficult-know-order
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Pupils often find it difficult to know what order logic gates should be
  evaluated. Without brackets, there is still an order of precedence."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Remind pupils of how the order of precedence in maths is applied to
  calculations. In a similarway, logic gates should be evaluated in the order: brackets,
  NOT, AND, OR."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.138947Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-better-check-hyperlinks-work-time
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """It is better to check that hyperlinks work each time you add a link instead of
  checking them at the end."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You should check the hyperlinks as you go to fix errors immediately but also
  check the whole product is working once you have finished. This will ensure that the
  product meets the brief and works in its entirety."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.139397Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-create-new-write-line-line
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You have to create a new write() line for each line you want to add to
  a file."""@en ;
  curric:correction """You can write mutiple lines in one write() statement. But if you want the
  text to appear on separate lines, you must use the new line character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141462Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-connect-motor-directly-microcontroller-work
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You can connect a motor directly to a microcontroller and it will work
  fine."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Microcontrollers send control signals, not power. Motor drivers act like
  electronic switches to take a signal and safely drive the motors with their own power
  supply."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141468Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-bitmap-raster-two-different-types
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Bitmap and raster are two different types of image."@en ;
  curric:correction "They are the same and can be referred to as a raster or bitmap image."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.141473Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-once-data-stored-database-its
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Once data is stored in a database, it’s automatically safe and private."@en ;
  curric:correction """Just storing data in a database does not make it secure. Data must be
  protected with proper privacy measures."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148496Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-logic-gates-two-inputs-one
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All logic gates have two inputs and one output."@en ;
  curric:correction """The number of inputs depends on the logic gate. The NOT gate is different in
  that it only has one input."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.148509Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cannot-prevent-things-going-wrong
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You cannot prevent things from going wrong in a project."@en ;
  curric:correction """Things can be done to prevent negative things happening during a project -
  these are called mitigations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-long-product-planned-matter-type
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As long as a product is planned, it does not matter which type of planning
  document is used."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It is important to use the correct planning document to ensure the planning
  stage is useful for the creating stage."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.149361Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-laws-stop-people-commiting-crimes
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Laws stop people commiting crimes."@en ;
  curric:correction """Laws are used to prosecute and may deter some individuals from committing
  crimes, but they do not stop laws being broken in the first place."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150645Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cloud-ensures-everyone-access-software
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The cloud ensures everyone can access software and resources."@en ;
  curric:correction """There are many different devices that can be used to access cloud services,
  and the functionality of each device will have an impact on the quality of service users
  will experience when using cloud based services."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.150950Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-devices-network-use-same-ip
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """All devices on a network use the same IP address, so there’s no need for
  private or public IPs or DNS."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Each device needs a unique private IP address on a local network. To access
  the internet, the router uses a public IP address. DNS translates website names into IP
  addresses so devices know where to send data."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.151747Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-last-stage-project-evaluation-conclusion
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "The last stage of the project evaluation is the conclusion."@en ;
  curric:correction """The last stage of the project evaluation is \"recommendations\". It is
  important to reflect on and learn from your experiences and say what could be improved and
  how."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154196Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-big-data-big-companies-organisations
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Big data is only for big companies or organisations."@en ;
  curric:correction """Businesses of all sizes can benefit from data analytics if they understand
  their goals and data needs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-embedded-system-computer-inside-computer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Embedded system is a computer inside a computer / system inside a system."@en ;
  curric:correction """Embedded systems are specific to a given task and often found within a
  machine."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154451Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-devices-automatically-know-communicate-other
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Devices automatically know how to communicate to any other device, regardless
  of brand or type, without needing specific rules."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Devices rely on shared protocols to communicate and exchange data
  effectively, like a common language or set of rules. This ensures all devices follow the
  same process."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154620Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-data-stored-cloud-doesnt-really
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Data is stored \"in the cloud\", so it doesn't really exist physically or have
  an environmental cost."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The cloud is a network of large data centres. These are real, physical
  facilities that consume huge amounts of energy and water, and generate significant
  e-waste."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-use-ide-write-run-programs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "You must use an IDE to write and run programs."@en ;
  curric:correction """You don’t need an IDE to write and run programs; you can use a simple text
  editor and a compiler or interpreter. However, an IDE makes the process much easier by
  providing tools such as autocompletion and error checking."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.154985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-testing-something-end-project
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Testing is something you only do at the end of a project."@en ;
  curric:correction """Testing is carried out throughout the development process. There are also
  specific stages and methods of testing that can be adopted. An overall approach to testing
  should be agreed and planned depending on the requirements of the system."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.155051Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-dont-need-consider-inputs-outputs
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """You don't need to consider the inputs, outputs and processes of a program
  during the analysis stage."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Listing the inputs, processes and outputs before coding helps you clearly
  understand what the program needs to do, avoid mistakes and save time later. It breaks the
  problem into smaller steps, making it easier to solve and explain to others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.156570Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-arrays-best-choice-storing-accessing
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Arrays are always the best choice for storing and accessing collections of
  data."""@en ;
  curric:correction """While arrays offer efficient direct access to elements using their index,
  they have limitations, such as fixed size and potential inefficiency in terms of unused
  elements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.158562Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-truth-table-column-headings-single
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """A truth table can only have the column headings of single inputs like A, B, or
  X."""@en ;
  curric:correction """A truth table can have column headings that calculate the value of the
  expression, for example (A OR B)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.158570Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-computational-thinking-techniques-related-solving
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Computational thinking techniques are only related to solving problems with
  computers."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The underlying principles of computational thinking can be applied in various
  aspects of life, even without any digital technology."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.161716Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-high-level-languages-better-low
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """High-level languages are always better than low-level languages because they
  are easier to use."""@en ;
  curric:correction """High-level languages are generally easier to learn and use. However,
  low-level languages offer more direct control over the computer's hardware, which can be
  essential for certain tasks like writing operating systems or device drivers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.161735Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-developing-code-project-your-own
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """If you are developing code for a project on your own, you don't need to worry
  about software design principles."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Even if your code isn't used by others, it is a good idea to follow software
  design principles in case you have to revisit or develop your code later on."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.162007Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-ram-stores-data-instructions-computer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "RAM stores data and instructions when a computer is switched off."@en ;
  curric:correction """RAM is volatile — when power is switched off, the data and instrucions are
  lost."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.162109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pseudocode-executed-computer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pseudocode can be executed by a computer."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pseudocode cannot be executed by a computer. Pseudocode must be translated
  into a real programming language such as Python, Java or C# for it to be executed by a
  computer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.162736Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-divisions-arranged-regular-rows-columns
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Divisions can only be arranged as regular rows and columns."@en ;
  curric:correction """By using divisions within other divisions any layout of a page is
  possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.162742Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-computers-use-same-operating-system
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "All computers use the same operating system."@en ;
  curric:correction """Different devices can run different operating systems, for example Windows,
  macOS, Linux, Android and iOS."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.164649Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-algorithmic-bias-completely-eliminated
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Algorithmic bias can be completely eliminated."@en ;
  curric:correction """It is extremely difficult, maybe impossible, for complex algorithms to be
  completely free from bias. By aiming to understand sources of bias, actively working to
  reduce it, and being transparent, algorithmic bias can be reduced as much as possible."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.164988Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-planning-isnt-needed-coding-projects
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Planning isn't needed for coding projects — you can just develop your code as
  you write."""@en ;
  curric:correction """If you plan out your algorithm first in human language, you can ensure each
  part is correct before writing any actual code. This reduces the likelihood of logic
  errors which could stop your code working as expected."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.165033Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-using-trace-tables-guarantees-correct
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Using trace tables guarantees correct logic and code."@en ;
  curric:correction """Trace tables can be subject to human error and can be impractical to use for
  complex algorithms."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.165042Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-logic-gates-limited-two-input
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """As logic gates are limited to two input, logic statements should also be
  limited in the same way."""@en ;
  curric:correction """Logic gates can be combined to created complex circuits that represent any
  number of logic statements combined."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.165834Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-evaluation-states-something-works
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "An evaluation just states if something works or not."@en ;
  curric:correction """A strong evaluation should be specific and evidence-based, covering what
  works, how this was achieved and how it was tested."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.165842Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-flowchart-created-writing-computer-program
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "A flowchart should always be created before writing a computer program."@en ;
  curric:correction """For simple programs, a flowchart may not be needed and could add to
  development time. Sometimes the program code itself might be clear enough without a
  flowchart."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.168917Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-pseudocode-directly-run-executed-computer
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Pseudocode can be directly run or executed by a computer."@en ;
  curric:correction """Pseudocode is a human-readable representation of an algorithm's logic but
  doesn't follow the syntax or rules of any particular programming language. It should only
  be used as a planning tool."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.169521Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-cpu-brain-computer-understands-instructions
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """The CPU is the brain of the computer and understands the instructions
  received."""@en ;
  curric:correction """The CPU is the core of the computer system and receives instructions that it
  then executes with the help of the different components."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.169528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-computational-thinking-means-writing-code
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Computational thinking means writing code for everything."@en ;
  curric:correction """While coding is a way to implement solutions, computational thinking can be
  applied to problems that don't require coding at all and should be seen as a set of
  processes that help people solve problems."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.169534Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-assembly-language-used-old-computers
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement """Assembly language is only used for very old computers, and it's not relevant
  to modern programming."""@en ;
  curric:correction """It's true that assembly was used more in the past, but it's still relevant.
  It gives direct hardware control, crucial for things like embedded systems and device
  drivers. Understanding it helps you see how computers work at a low level."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.169868Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-increasing-cores-clock-speed-improves
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Increasing cores and clock speed improves performance."@en ;
  curric:correction """It can improve performance but not always, as other hardware components may
  not be able to work that way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.169876Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:misconception-algorithms-computer-programs-actually-same
  a curric:Misconception ;
  curric:statement "Algorithms and computer programs are actually the same thing."@en ;
  curric:correction """A computer program is a specific implementation of an algorithm's logic. A
  clearly written algorithm provides instructions that can be implemented in various ways
  including, but not limited to, computer programs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:15.169885Z"^^xsd:dateTime .
